Defendant Lashun T McGee in court, in custody, with attorney Daniel P. Murray.   Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Murray advises of corrections to the presentence investigation report.  Arguments by the State.  Statement by T. Hofer.  Statements by defendant.  Arguments by the Defense.    

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

9 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 252 days)
  -  4 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  5 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*No possession of any weapons
*Successfully complete Cognitive Intervention Programming (CGIP) classes
*Complete all other programming deemed appropriate by the Department of Corrections

RESTITUTION:  $0 ;

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
